00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Here's what science actually says about p values nuance.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:09,200
P values determine if results are statistically significant, but the story doesn’t end there.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:15,600
A p value below 0.05 often gets all the attention, but it’s not a magic threshold.

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:22,800
It can’t tell us how important or relevant a finding is—only if it’s unlikely to occur by chance.

5
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:28,400
So, when you hear p values, remember: context matters, and results can always vary.

